```latex
\documentclass{standalone}
\usepackage{tikz}

\begin{document}

\begin{tikzpicture}[scale=2]
    % Draw the labeled (blue) area
    \fill[blue] (-1,-1) rectangle (1,1);

    % Draw the unlabeled (gray) area
    \draw[gray] (-3,-3) rectangle (3,3);

    % Add labels for clarity
    \node at (-2,-2) [below left] {Unlabeled Data};
    \node at (0,0) [below right] {Labeled Data};
\end{tikzpicture}

\end{document}
```

### Explanation:
- **Blue Area**: This represents the labeled data. It is filled with blue color.
- **Gray Area**: This represents the unlabeled data. It is outlined in gray color but not filled.
- **Labels**: "Unlabeled Data" and "Labeled Data" are added below the respective areas to provide context.

